    "It can be noted that this batching may induce false positives to the advantage of SciFinder, but also considerably accelerates the querying process.",
    "In SciFinder, ions are stored together with their counterion as one unique compound.",
    "Then, charged molecules can not be matched using their InChIKey.",
    "Therefore, queries of charged molecules are instead done using the SciFinder molecule editor, which allows the import of SMILES strings and, ultimately, correctly retrieves charged molecules.",
    "SciFinder does not allow to distinguish molecules extracted from text or images, and the matched patent documents can be any patent from the patent family of the query."
